The paper deals with the application of machine learning methods for the classification of Transposable Elements (TEs). The paper discusses the limitations of existing methods and proposes a new approach using Support Vector Machines (SVM). This work involves the use of various ML algorithms and techniques, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), databases (cs.DB), computational evolution (cs.CE), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
